Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.667 --> 00:00:03.669
HEY, ALL I KNOW IS ITS GOOD

00:00:03.702 --> 00:00:05.571
HAVING ANOTHER BROTHER
MOVE INTO THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

00:00:05.604 --> 00:00:07.507
- HEY, MAN, IT'S GOOD
TO HAVE YOU OVER.

00:00:07.540 --> 00:00:09.342
AND I THINK
THAT YOU WILL DIG THIS.

00:00:09.375 --> 00:00:12.512
- ALL RIGHT.

00:00:12.545 --> 00:00:14.480
HEY!
- HUH?

00:00:14.513 --> 00:00:16.049
- NICE GUITAR COLLECTION.
- OH, THANKS, MAN.

00:00:16.082 --> 00:00:18.484
HEY, YOU WANNA HEAR SOMETHING?

00:00:18.517 --> 00:00:20.386
- YEAH, SURE.
- ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

00:00:20.419 --> 00:00:21.788
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GET THIS STARTED.

00:00:21.821 --> 00:00:22.922
LET'S GET THIS STARTED.

00:00:22.955 --> 00:00:24.991
[playing guitar]

00:00:25.024 --> 00:00:27.827
♪ WELL, I'M JUST
A GOOD OLD AMERICAN BOY ♪

00:00:27.860 --> 00:00:32.665
♪ WITH A HEART
THAT'S RED, WHITE, AND TRUE ♪

00:00:32.698 --> 00:00:35.034
♪ I'M DREAMIN' OF THE GIRL
WITH THE RED HAIR AND FRECKLES ♪

00:00:35.067 --> 00:00:38.304
♪ AND HER EYES LIKE
THE SKIES OF BLUE ♪

00:00:38.337 --> 00:00:40.239
- COUNTRY MUSIC.

00:00:40.272 --> 00:00:41.340
- YEAH, I GREW UP IN TEXAS.
YOU KNOW, SO...

00:00:41.373 --> 00:00:43.176
- ALL RIGHT.

00:00:43.209 --> 00:00:44.911
- ♪ KEEP HER SAFE
FROM THE HOMIES ♪

00:00:44.944 --> 00:00:47.113
♪ IN THE WRONG SIDE
OF TOWN ♪

00:00:47.146 --> 00:00:50.750
♪ WHERE THEY'RE SMOKIN' THE
REEFER AND ACTING LIKE CLOWNS ♪

00:00:50.783 --> 00:00:53.586
♪ KEEP THAT PRETTY WHITE DRESS
FROM GETTING DIRTY AND BROWN ♪

00:00:53.619 --> 00:00:55.955
♪ 'CAUSE THAT'S
THE AMERICAN WAY ♪

00:00:58.958 --> 00:01:00.460
WOO-HOO!

00:01:00.493 --> 00:01:02.628
- WHOA.

00:01:02.661 --> 00:01:03.796
PRETTY RACIST SONG.

00:01:03.829 --> 00:01:05.398
[both laugh]

00:01:05.431 --> 00:01:07.633
- RACIST?
AGAINST WHO?

00:01:07.666 --> 00:01:09.602
- BLACK PEOPLE.
- BLACK PEOPLE?

00:01:09.635 --> 00:01:11.471
BUT I'M BLACK.
[laughs]

00:01:11.504 --> 00:01:13.739
- WELL, KEEPING
THE REDHEADED GIRL AWAY

00:01:13.772 --> 00:01:15.441
FROM THE HOMIES
ON THE WRONG SIDE OF TOWN?

00:01:15.474 --> 00:01:17.443
- HOMIES?

00:01:17.476 --> 00:01:19.278
COME ON, BROTHER.
THERE'S ALL KINDS OF HOMIES.

00:01:19.311 --> 00:01:22.448
YOU KNOW, WHITE HOMIES,
ASIAN HOMIES.

00:01:22.481 --> 00:01:24.383
- NO, HOMIES ARE BLACK.

00:01:24.416 --> 00:01:25.685
- NO, I THINK YOU'RE
MAKING THEM BLACK, MAN.

00:01:25.718 --> 00:01:27.854
I THINK THAT'S YOUR STUFF.

00:01:27.887 --> 00:01:31.357
YOU HEAR THE TWANG AND THEN
YOU ASSUME THAT IT'S RACIST.

00:01:31.390 --> 00:01:33.626
BUT THAT'S JUST
WHAT COUNTRY MUSIC IS LIKE.

00:01:33.659 --> 00:01:35.428
HERE, LOOK, YOU'RE
GONNA LIKE THIS ONE.

00:01:35.461 --> 00:01:37.096
YOU'LL LIKE THIS ONE.
- ALL RIGHT.

00:01:37.129 --> 00:01:39.532
- [playing guitar]

00:01:39.565 --> 00:01:42.235
♪ SOME FOLKS WEAR THEIR HATS
WAY OFF TO THE SIDE ♪

00:01:42.268 --> 00:01:45.404
♪ WITH THEIR PANTS DOWN LOW
AND A GUN TUCKED INSIDE ♪

00:01:45.437 --> 00:01:48.207
♪ TAKE THEIR BEER BY THE 40
AND THEIR CHICKEN DEEP-FRIED ♪

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:53.045
♪ I THINK WE ALL KNOW
WHO WE'RE TALKING ABOUT ♪

00:01:53.078 --> 00:01:55.781
♪ THE ONLY DARK I LIKE
IS WHEN I TURN OFF THE LIGHTS ♪

00:01:55.814 --> 00:01:59.051
♪ THE ONLY HOOD I LOVE
IS POINTY AND WHITE ♪

00:01:59.084 --> 00:02:00.653
♪ CAN'T TRUST YOU
IF I CAN'T ♪

00:02:00.686 --> 00:02:02.755
♪ SEE YOUR FACE
AT NIGHT ♪

00:02:02.788 --> 00:02:04.590
♪ I THINK WE ALL KNOW
WHO WE'RE TALKING ABOUT ♪

00:02:04.623 --> 00:02:05.625
- ALL RIGHT, WAIT. HEY!

00:02:05.658 --> 00:02:07.226
STOP THAT.

00:02:07.259 --> 00:02:09.095
THAT'S RACIST.

00:02:09.128 --> 00:02:11.063
- WHAT'S--WHAT?
WHAT IS RACIST ABOUT IT?

00:02:11.096 --> 00:02:13.199
- "THE ONLY HOOD I LOVE
IS POINTY AND WHITE"?

00:02:13.232 --> 00:02:15.034
- YEAH, MAN.

00:02:15.067 --> 00:02:17.103
- THAT'S TALKING
ABOUT THE KLAN, MAN.

00:02:17.136 --> 00:02:21.073
- THE KU KLUX KLAN?
ARE YOU OUTSIDE OF YOUR MIND?

00:02:21.106 --> 00:02:23.676
THAT'S TRADITIONAL
COUNTRY MUSIC IMAGERY, MAN,

00:02:23.709 --> 00:02:26.546
LIKE A PICKUP TRUCK
OR SLEEPING UNDER THE STARS,

00:02:26.579 --> 00:02:27.947
OR YOUR DOG GOT KILLED
OR YOUR WIFE LEFT YOU.

00:02:27.980 --> 00:02:30.016
SAME THING!

00:02:30.049 --> 00:02:31.984
- I WOULD HAVE BEEN FINE
WITH ANY OF THOSE THINGS.

00:02:32.017 --> 00:02:33.252
- WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN THOSE THINGS

00:02:33.285 --> 00:02:34.487
AND WHAT IS IN THE SONG?

00:02:34.520 --> 00:02:36.556
- THEY'RE NOT RACIAL!

00:02:36.589 --> 00:02:37.823
- HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
CAN I JUST SAY SOMETHING, MAN?

00:02:37.856 --> 00:02:39.759
I'M JUST GONNA BE FRANK.

00:02:39.792 --> 00:02:41.494
YOU'RE GETTING A LITTLE,
LIKE, AL SHARPTON,

00:02:41.527 --> 00:02:43.396
LIKE, FARRAKHAN
ON ME RIGHT NOW.

00:02:43.429 --> 00:02:45.665
- OH, MY GOD.
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

00:02:45.698 --> 00:02:48.534
- YO, DUDE, DUDE, PLEASE.
HEY, CAN I DO ONE MORE?

00:02:48.567 --> 00:02:50.636
LET ME JUST
DO ONE MORE, DOG.

00:02:50.669 --> 00:02:54.607
I ABSOLUTELY PROMISE YOU
THAT THIS SONG IS NOT RACIST

00:02:54.640 --> 00:02:59.612
AND IT'S IMPOSSIBLE FOR YOU
TO MISINTERPRET IT AS SUCH.

00:02:59.645 --> 00:03:01.347
- OKAY, IT SEEMS LIKE
YOU'RE ABOUT TO SING

00:03:01.380 --> 00:03:03.216
THE MOST RACIST SONG
SO FAR.

00:03:03.249 --> 00:03:06.619
- I'M NOT.

00:03:06.652 --> 00:03:08.921
♪ HIDEY-LIDEY-LIDEY-LEE ♪

00:03:08.954 --> 00:03:10.923
♪ GET ME A ROPE
AND FIND ME A TREE ♪

00:03:10.956 --> 00:03:14.260
- OKAY, I'M OUT.

00:03:14.293 --> 00:03:15.461
- COME ON, MAN. HEY!

00:03:15.494 --> 00:03:17.496
SHOOT.

00:03:17.529 --> 00:03:21.067
I'M OVER HERE TRYING
TO SING ABOUT A TIRE SWING.

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:23.569
GONNA WRITE OFF
AN ENTIRE GENRE OF MUSIC.

00:03:23.602 --> 00:03:25.771
[playing guitar]

00:03:25.804 --> 00:03:28.708
♪ THE BANJOS ARE STRUMMING,
AND THE DRUMS ARE A-BANGIN' ♪

00:03:28.741 --> 00:03:32.245
♪ LET'S GET THE BOYS TOGETHER
AND HAVE OURSELVES A-HANGIN' ♪

00:03:32.278 --> 00:03:34.247
OH, DAMN.

00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:37.483
NOW I SEE IT.
NOW I SEE IT.

